From 5b52f1d87564addde7fbf7183477e8a053fda576 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aloka Dixit <aloka.dixit@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jul 2025 10:58:54 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:wifi:mac80211: fix FILS discovery clean-up

Fils discovery and unsolicited broadcast probe response
templates are deleted during stop_ap() but the intervals
are not reset which can cause issue when the drivers
try template retrieval based on non-zero interval values.

Reset the interval for proper clean-up.

Patch-dependency: none

Signed-off-by: Aloka Dixit <aloka.dixit@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/cfg.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/cfg.c b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
index 4bf84489471f..b2cea6659425 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/cfg.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
@@ -1917,6 +1917,10 @@ static int ieee80211_stop_ap(struct wiphy *wiphy, struct net_device *dev,
 	if (old_unsol_bcast_probe_resp)
 		kfree_rcu(old_unsol_bcast_probe_resp, rcu_head);
 
+	link_conf->fils_discovery.min_interval = 0;
+	link_conf->fils_discovery.max_interval = 0;
+	link_conf->unsol_bcast_probe_resp_interval = 0;
+
 	/* Reset active flag only for the last link */
 	if (!ieee80211_num_beaconing_links(sdata))
 		sdata->u.ap.active = false;
-- 
2.34.1

